For a simple calculator program as a beginner, I would recommend either Python or JavaScript.

Python:
- Is an easy to learn language for beginners 
- Has a simple syntax with little boilerplate code
- Has good support for numeric calculations and math functions

A simple Python calculator program would look something like this:

```python
# Get input from the user
num1 = float(input("Enter first number: "))  
num2 = float(input("Enter second number: "))

# Get the operation from the user    
op = input("Enter operator (+, -, * or /):")

# Perform calculation based on the operation    
if op == "+":
   print(num1 + num2)

elif op == "-":      
   print(num1 - num2)

elif op == "*":
   print(num1 * num2)

elif op == "/":
   print(num1 / num2)
```

JavaScript:
- Is the language of the web, so is very useful to learn 
- Also has a simple syntax and is easy to pickup for beginners
- Has built-in Math object to perform calculations

A simple JavaScript calculator would be:

```js
let num1 = parseFloat(prompt("Enter first number: ")); 
let num2 = parseFloat(prompt("Enter second number: "));
let op = prompt("Enter operator (+, -, * or /): ");

if(op == "+") {
  alert( num1 + num2 );
} else if(op == "-") {
  alert( num1 - num2 ); 
} else if(op == "*") {
  alert( num1 * num2 );
} else {
  alert( num1 / num2 );
}
```

So in summary, I would recommend either Python or JavaScript for a simple calculator program as a beginner. Let me know if you have any other questions!
